H0.text: In medicine, if something is subcutaneous it is applied or located under which organ of the body. Muscle

H1.text: In medicine, if something is subcutaneous it is applied or located under which organ of the body. Fat

H2.text: In medicine, if something is subcutaneous it is applied or located under which organ of the body. Bone

H3.text: In medicine, if something is subcutaneous it is applied or located under which organ of the body. Skin

A4.text: The subcutaneous tissue is the lowermost layer of the integumentary system in vertebrates.

A5.text: Subcutaneous fat is found just beneath the skin.
